    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-12-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-12-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="399"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d399">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <gloss target="#t_CFM1">C.F.M.</gloss> Files: Lot M–88: Box 2079: <gloss
                        target="#t_CFM1">CFM</gloss> Documents</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Proposal by the <gloss type="from">French Delegation</gloss>
                        to the <gloss type="to">Council of Foreign Ministers</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="55" xml:id="d399fn55">This proposal was considered by the Council of
                        Foreign Ministers at its 19th Meeting, December 9, 1946; see the United
                        States Delegation Minutes, <ref target="#pg_1481">p. 1481</ref>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <gloss target="#t_CFM46NY1">CFM(46)(NY)</gloss>63</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">New York</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-12-07">December 7,
                            1946</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Questions Relating to Germany</hi>
                </p>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">draft agenda for the next session of the council of foreign
                        ministers</hi>
                </p>
                <list>
                    <label>1)</label>
                    <item>Future frontiers of Germany.</item>
                    <label>2)</label>
                    <item>Control measures for ensuring European security. <list>
                            <item>—United States Draft of Four Power Treaty.</item>
                            <item>—other measures for economic and military control.</item>
                        </list>
                    </item>
                    <label>3)</label>
                    <item>Consideration of French proposals for the Ruhr and Rhineland in relation
                        to items 1 and 2.</item>
                    <label>4)</label>
                    <item>Consideration of a report to be obtained from Allied Control Authority in
                        Berlin dealing with: <list>
                            <item>—demilitarization of Germany,</item>
                            <item>—democratization and denazification,</item>
                            <item>—reparation,</item>
                            <item>—economic unity and central agencies as well as provisional
                                political organization of Germany under quadripartite
                                Government.</item>
                        </list>
                    </item>
                    <label>5)</label>
                    <item>General outline of a permanent political organization for Germany.</item>
                    <label>6)</label>
                    <item>Consideration of a report from the Allied Control Authority in Berlin on
                        the liquidation of Prussia.</item>
                    <label>7)</label>
                    <item>Consideration of the report already submitted by the Committee of Coal
                        Experts.</item>
                    <label>8)</label>
                    <item>General outline of the Peace Treaty with Germany.</item>
                    <label>9)</label>
                    <item>Treaty with Austria and related matters.</item>
                    <label>10)</label>
                    <item>Limitation of European occupation forces.</item>
                </list>
            </div>
